This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with stereo disparity estimation, which is a common task in computer vision. The use of a recurrent model also suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The paper also mentions the use of a soft attention mechanism, which is a common technique in computer vision and machine learning. The task of stereo matching is also relevant to robotics (cs.RO) as it is important for depth perception in autonomous systems. Finally, the paper mentions the use of benchmarks such as KITTI and Middlebury, which are commonly used in computer vision and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CVPR) research.
